16namespace v8 {
17namespace internal {
18
19class ArrayBufferExtension;
20class Heap;
21
22// Singly linked-list of ArrayBufferExtensions that stores head and tail of the
23// list to allow for concatenation of lists.
24struct ArrayBufferList final {
25 bool IsEmpty() const;
26 size_t ApproximateBytes() const { return bytes_; }
27 size_t BytesSlow() const;
28
29 void Append(ArrayBufferExtension* extension);
30 void Append(ArrayBufferList& list);
31
32 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE bool ContainsSlow(ArrayBufferExtension* extension) const;
33
34 private:
35 ArrayBufferExtension* head_ = nullptr;
36 ArrayBufferExtension* tail_ = nullptr;
37 // Bytes are approximate as they may be subtracted eagerly, while the
38 // `ArrayBufferExtension` is still in the list. The extension will only be
39 // dropped on next sweep.
40 size_t bytes_ = 0;
41
42 friend class ArrayBufferSweeper;
43};
44
45// The ArrayBufferSweeper iterates and deletes ArrayBufferExtensions
46// concurrently to the application.
47class ArrayBufferSweeper final {
48 public:
49 enum class SweepingType { kYoung, kFull };
50 enum class TreatAllYoungAsPromoted { kNo, kYes };
51
52 explicit ArrayBufferSweeper(Heap* heap);
53 ~ArrayBufferSweeper();
54
55 void RequestSweep(SweepingType sweeping_type,
56 TreatAllYoungAsPromoted treat_all_young_as_promoted);
57 void EnsureFinished();
58
59 // Track the given ArrayBufferExtension for the given JSArrayBuffer.
60 void Append(Tagged<JSArrayBuffer> object, ArrayBufferExtension* extension);
61
62 // Detaches an ArrayBufferExtension from a JSArrayBuffer.
63 void Detach(Tagged<JSArrayBuffer> object, ArrayBufferExtension* extension);
64
65 const ArrayBufferList& young() const { return young_; }
66 const ArrayBufferList& old() const { return old_; }
67
68 // Bytes accounted in the young generation. Rebuilt during sweeping.
69 size_t YoungBytes() const { return young().ApproximateBytes(); }
70 // Bytes accounted in the old generation. Rebuilt during sweeping.
71 size_t OldBytes() const { return old().ApproximateBytes(); }
72
73 bool sweeping_in_progress() const { return state_.get(); }
74
75 uint64_t GetTraceIdForFlowEvent(GCTracer::Scope::ScopeId scope_id) const;
76
77 private:
78 class SweepingState;
79
80 // Finishes sweeping if it is already done.
81 void FinishIfDone();
82 void Finish();
83
84 // Increments external memory counters outside of ArrayBufferSweeper.
85 // Increment may trigger GC.
86 void IncrementExternalMemoryCounters(size_t bytes);
87 void DecrementExternalMemoryCounters(size_t bytes);
88
89 void Prepare(SweepingType type,
90 TreatAllYoungAsPromoted treat_all_young_as_promoted,
91 uint64_t trace_id);
92 void Finalize();
93
94 void ReleaseAll(ArrayBufferList* extension);
95
96 static void FinalizeAndDelete(ArrayBufferExtension* extension);
97
98 Heap* const heap_;
99 std::unique_ptr<SweepingState> state_;
100 ArrayBufferList young_;
101 ArrayBufferList old_;
102};
103
104} // namespace internal
105} // namespace v8
